					<item>
				<guid>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-7948440#post-4023358</guid>
				<title>Loved it!</title>
				<link>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-7948440/error:field-cannot-be-lloyd#post-4023358</link>
				<description></description>
				<pubDate>Sat, 13 Oct 2018 23:06:27 +0000</pubDate>
				<wikidot:authorName>CoffeeCannon</wikidot:authorName>				<wikidot:authorUserId>4394502</wikidot:authorUserId>				<content:encoded>
					<![CDATA[
						 <p>I mean, I saw it coming, but I love how it ties in the other 001 proposal and actually twists it into something more sinister (if I'm understanding correctly). By actively getting everyone outside and helping along the situation, the foundation is damning even more people to the sun. But I guess it's worth it for Lloyd stability?</p> 
				 	]]>
				</content:encoded>							</item>
					<item>
				<guid>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-7948440#post-4022245</guid>
				<title>Very Nice</title>
				<link>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-7948440/error:field-cannot-be-lloyd#post-4022245</link>
				<description></description>
				<pubDate>Fri, 12 Oct 2018 17:06:35 +0000</pubDate>
				<wikidot:authorName>Genamako</wikidot:authorName>				<wikidot:authorUserId>2684240</wikidot:authorUserId>				<content:encoded>
					<![CDATA[
						 <p>I had a concept for a tale like this detailing the events leading up to &quot;When Day Breaks.&quot; Mine more or less followed the week before the event occured but this one was rather well made! My personal belief of the canon is rather similar to this tale too. The writing of it was pretty solid albiet a bit bland in some areas. The characters, while not too in depth and rather 2 dimensional at times, were pleasant for the most part. Overall I enjoyed this.</p> 
				 	]]>
				</content:encoded>							</item>
